item.title: CVE-2017-17224|2024-08-05T20:43:59.900Z -- huawei -- hg655m
item.description: Some Huawei smart phones with versions earlier than Harry-AL00C 9.1.0.206(C00E205R3P1) have a null pointer dereference vulnerability. An attacker crafts specific packets and sends to the affected product to exploit this vulnerability. Successful exploitation may cause the affected phone abnormal.
